r that pleasures have to be repudiated and annoyances accepted. The wise man therefore always holds in these matters to this principle of selection: he rejects pleasures to secure other greater pleasures, or else he endures pains to avoid worse pains.\"', 3, NULL, 0, 1, '2026-02-25 18:15:27', '2026-02-25 18:15:40');
